The paper deals with synthesizing location traces while protecting users' privacy, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed method involves factorization and sampling, which are common techniques in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the analysis of spatial big data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
